Description: USB encryption enforcement daemon with content scanning (bundled)
 A system daemon that enforces encryption requirements on USB storage devices
 and scans files for sensitive data before allowing writes to removable media.
 .
 This package includes bundled Python dependencies and does NOT require
 internet access during installation. Suitable for offline/airgapped
 environments.
 .
 Features:
  - Automatic detection of USB storage devices
  - Encryption requirement enforcement
  - Content scanning for sensitive data (SSN, credit cards, API keys, etc.)
  - FUSE overlay filesystem with real-time scanning
  - Archive scanning (ZIP, 7z, RAR, tar)
  - Document scanning (PDF, DOCX, XLSX, PPTX)
  - User notifications via GUI with progress tracking
  - Integration with udev, systemd, and DBus
  - Configuration via TOML file
  - Bundled Python dependencies (pyudev, pydbus, fusepy, pdfplumber, etc.)
